Rev Dr '''Nigel G. Wright''' (13 May 1949) is a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[Baptist]] theologian..<ref name="Sprinkle">{{cite book|author=Stephen Sprinkle|title=Ordination: Celebrating the Gift of Min|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=jta75EzFrp8C&pg=PA37|publisher=Chalice Press|isbn=978-0-8272-2744-6|pages=37<U+2013>}}</ref>

==Early life and education==
Wright was born in [[Manchester, United Kingdom|Manchester]], and joined the Baptist Church at the age of fifteen. He attended the University of Leeds, graduating in 1970 with a B. A.  He earned a M. Th. degree from the University of Glasgow 19 1987 and a Ph. D. in 1994 from King's College, London.<ref name="Garrett2009">{{cite book|author=James Leo Garrett|title=Baptist Theology: A Four-century Study|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=epEHq0mTsKgC&pg=PA686|year=2009|publisher=Mercer University Press|isbn=978-0-88146-129-9|pages=686<U+2013>}}</ref>

==Career in the Baptist Church==
Wright served as a Baptist minister, and later became principal of Spurgeon's College, London.<ref name="Fitz-GibbonFitz-Gibbon2012">{{cite book|author1=Jane Fitz-Gibbon|author2=Andrew Fitz-Gibbon|title=Secular Monasticism: A Journey|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=7b4yjRGQSi4C&pg=PA27|date=1 September 2012|publisher=Xlibris Corporation|isbn=978-1-4797-0719-5|pages=27<U+2013>}}</ref>

==Author and theologian==
Wright has written a number of books<ref name="Sell2012">{{cite book|author=Alan P.F. Sell|title=Nonconformist Theology in the Twentieth Century|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=qHxNAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA105|date=17 September 2012|publisher=Wipf and Stock Publishers|isbn=978-1-62032-422-6|pages=105<U+2013>}}</ref><ref name="Wright2006">{{cite book|author=Christopher J. H. Wright|title=The Mission of God: Unlocking the Bible's Grand Narrative|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=gIeCwHb3OsQC&pg=PA433|date=23 October 2006|publisher=InterVarsity Press|isbn=978-0-8308-2571-4|pages=433<U+2013>}}</ref>  and essays<ref name="CohenParsons2011">{{cite book|author1=David J. Cohen|author2=Michael Parsons|title=Beyond 400: Exploring Baptist Futures|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=sXxMAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA237|date=1 January 2011|publisher=Wipf and Stock Publishers|isbn=978-1-60899-337-6|pages=237<U+2013>}}</ref> on various Baptist theological topics.<ref name="Yarnell2013">{{cite book|author=Malcolm B. Yarnell|title=The Anabaptists and Contemporary Baptists: Restoring New Testament Christianity|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=QhRkAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA178|date=15 September 2013|publisher=B&H Publishing Group|isbn=978-1-4336-8174-5|pages=178<U+2013>}}</ref>  His views are summarized in ''Free Church, Free State: The Positive Baptist Vision'', published by Milton Keynes in 2005.<ref name="Holmes2012">{{cite book|author=Stephen R. Holmes|title=Baptist Theology|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=IT91FUoL7HsC&pg=PA168|date=19 April 2012|publisher=A&C Black|isbn=978-0-567-00031-6|pages=168<U+2013>}}</ref><ref name="RandallPilli2006">{{cite book|author1=Ian M. Randall|author2=Toivo Pilli|author3=Anthony Cross|title=Baptist Identities: International Studies from the Seventeenth to the Twentieth Centuries|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=N7NLAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA377|date=1 August 2006|publisher=Wipf & Stock Publishers|isbn=978-1-59752-833-7|pages=377<U+2013>}}</ref>  His writings have been widely cited and discussed by other theologians.<ref name="DareWoodman2011">{{cite book|author1=Helen Dare|author2=Simon Patrick Woodman|title=The "plainly Revealed" Word of God?: Baptist Hermeneutics in Theory and Practice|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=zq0QQLGKPSQC&pg=PA154|year=2011|publisher=Mercer University Press|isbn=978-0-88146-237-1|pages=154<U+2013>}}</ref><ref name="Scott2014">{{cite book|author=Benjamin G. McNair Scott|title=Apostles Today: Making Sense of Contemporary Charismatic Apostolates: A Historical and Theological Appraisal|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=5Q-QBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA44|date=2 June 2014|publisher=Wipf and Stock Publishers|isbn=978-1-62564-118-2|pages=44<U+2013>}}</ref>

Wright is also a frequent speaker and presenter about Baptist theological renewal.<ref name="Hocken2009">{{cite book|author=Peter Hocken|title=The Challenges of the Pentecostal, Charismatic, and Messianic Jewish Movements: The Tensions of the Spirit|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=Ziw73-alUrMC&pg=PA64|year=2009|publisher=Ashgate Publishing, Ltd.|isbn=978-0-7546-6746-9|pages=64<U+2013>}}</ref>

On his retirement, he was honored by a [[festschrift]]: Lalleman, Pieter J, and David Coffey.'' Challenging to Change: Dialogues with a Radical Baptist Theologian: Essays Presented to Dr. Nigel G. Wright on His Sixtieth Birthday.'' London: Spurgeon's College, 2009. ISBN  9780950068237<ref name=wcf>[http://www.worldcat.org/title/challenging-to-change-dialogues-with-a-radical-baptist-theologian-essays-presented-to-dr-nigel-g-wright-on-his-sixtieth-birthday/oclc/436970327&referer=brief_results   WorldCat]</ref>

==Publications==
*Wright, Nigel. ''Free Church, Free State: The Positive Baptist Vision.'' Milton Keynes, UK: Paternoster, 2005. ISBN 9781842273531
*Wright, Nigel G. ''Power and Discipleship: Towards a Baptist Theology of the State.''  Oxford: Whitley Publications, 1996. ISBN 9780952815013 (The Whitley Lecture for 1996-97.)
*Wright, Nigel. ''The Fair Face of Evil: Putting the Power of Darkness in Its Place''. London: Marshall Pickering, 1989. ISBN 9780551017863
*Wright, Nigel. '' God on the Inside: The Holy Spirit in Holy Scripture.'' Oxford: Bible Reading Fellowship, 2006. ISBN 9781841014845
*Wright, Nigel. ''Baptist Basics.'' 12 vols.  Didcot: Baptist Union of Great Britain, 2009.

